In Germany about 41% of malignant neoplasies of women are carcinomas of mamma, cervix, Corpus uteri and ovary. Therapy of these malignomas consists of surgery, radio-, chemo- or hormonotherapy. Apart from therapeutic effects primary therapy may have negative effects in different physical, psychical and social aspects. These side effects are the concern of stationary oncological rehabilitation. Interdisciplinary cooperation makes it possible to consider the individual requirements of the patient.  
